pliance, state-specific caregiver-consent compliance, 42 CFR Part 2 compliance where applicable, state-specific mental-health and HIV record protections compliance, full Information Blocking and Interoperability rule alignment, full per-cohort equity monitoring with launch-gate discipline, mandatory-reporting routing per state, outcome-correlation pipeline with multi-window correlation against referral-closure, transition-of-care-completion, medication-reconciliation accuracy, readmission-rate, and ED-utilization-rate trajectories, named operational owners across primary care, hospital medicine, specialty practice, pharmacy, home health, care management, the licensed-care-manager workforce, compliance, regulatory, IT, the call center, patient experience, and (in some institutions) the equity and patient-advocacy office | 30-48 months |
